<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-273-508  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 273 508.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  April 3 1989 v3 n14 p9(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Army begins use of air defense system at White Sands.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Reed, Fred.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The second Air Defense Anti-Tank System (ADATS), acomputer-controlled missile battery mounted on an M-3 BradleyFighting Vehicle, has been delivered to White Sands Missile Range.andO;ADATS features a search radar with a 12-mile range which can beturned off without disabling ADATS, making the unitnon-susceptible to anti-radiation missiles that home in on energyemissions.andP;  Targets are handed off to passive sensors that do notemit energy.andP;  An electro-optical module integrates the passivesensors, a laser range-finder and a guidance laser for eightMach-3 missiles carried by each ADATS unit.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. ArmyMilitaryWeapons.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>